    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-11-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-11-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="397"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111A Ports/54a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to <gloss
                            type="to">Diplomatic Officers in the American Republics</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-07">November 7,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sirs</hi>: The Department of State has been informed by the
                    British Embassy that a considerable number of British merchant vessels are being
                    equipped with fighter aircraft to be used solely for defensive purposes. The
                    Embassy stated:</p>
                <p>[Here follows text of paragraph 3 (with the omission of the first two sentences),
                    paragraph 4, and paragraph 5 of the British <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi>
                    of April 7, 1941, printed on <ref target="#pg_387">page 387</ref>.]</p>
                <p>The Department of State replied to the British Embassy on July 24, 1941, as
                    follows:</p>
                <p>[Here follows the text of the second paragraph of <hi rend="italic"
                        >aide-mémoire</hi> to the British Embassy, dated July 24, 1941, printed on
                        <ref target="#pg_392">page 392</ref>.]</p>
                <p>You are requested to bring the foregoing to the attention of the government to
                    which you are accredited.</p>
                <p>Very truly yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cordell Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
